  "prompt": "How has legislation evolved to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Legislation to combat money laundering has evolved significantly over time:\n\n1. Early Stages\n- Initial focus on drug-related financial crimes\n- Limited international cooperation\n- Minimal regulatory frameworks\n\n2. Key Milestones\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970, US)\n- First international anti-money laundering guidelines by FATF (1989)\n- United Nations Convention against Illicit Drugs (1988)\n\n3. Expanding Scope\n- Broadened definition of money laundering\n- Increased reporting requirements\n- Enhanced customer due diligence regulations\n\n4. Modern Developments\n- Stricter Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Advanced digital transaction monitoring\n- Cryptocurrency-specific regulations\n- Increased international collaboration\n\n5. Technological Adaptations\n- Machine learning for suspicious activity detection\n- Blockchain tracking capabilities\n- Real-time transaction screening\n- Cross-border information sharing platforms\n\n6. Recent Trends\n- Focusing on beneficial ownership transparency\n- Combating terrorist financing\n- Addressing emerging digital financial technologies\n- Implementing more comprehensive risk-based approaches\n\nThe legislative landscape continues evolving to address increasingly complex financial crime methods.",
